514
00:55:49,555 --> 00:55:51,307
Upstairs, Mr. White.

515
00:56:01,734 --> 00:56:05,488
I always knew death would
wear a familiar face,

516
00:56:05,571 --> 00:56:07,073
but not yours.

517
00:56:07,156 --> 00:56:10,076
To what do I owe
this pleasure, Mr. Bond?

518
00:56:12,453 --> 00:56:14,747
I was at a meeting recently

519
00:56:14,830 --> 00:56:16,707
and your name came up.

520
00:56:16,832 --> 00:56:19,794
I'm flattered London is
still talking about me.

521
00:56:19,877 --> 00:56:21,337
It wasn't MI6.

522
00:56:22,421 --> 00:56:23,714
It was Rome.

523
00:56:24,924 --> 00:56:26,884
Your team, not mine.

524
00:56:27,259 --> 00:56:28,260
Ah.

525
00:56:32,932 --> 00:56:37,269
Last month,
I found thallium in my cell phone.

526
00:56:37,770 --> 00:56:41,899
It's done its job.
I have a few weeks.
Maybe less.

527
00:56:44,318 --> 00:56:47,321
So, here we are, Mr. Bond,

528
00:56:47,738 --> 00:56:50,449
two dead men
enjoying the evening.

529
00:56:51,200 --> 00:56:52,743
What did you do?

530
00:56:52,785 --> 00:56:54,412
I disobeyed him.

531
00:56:54,745 --> 00:56:58,249
I followed him
as far as I could.

532
00:56:58,958 --> 00:57:00,209
He changed.

533
00:57:00,584 --> 00:57:01,877
Oh, I see.

534
00:57:02,628 --> 00:57:04,213
You grew a conscience.

535
00:57:04,755 --> 00:57:07,716
Our game is our game.
But this?

536
00:57:08,717 --> 00:57:10,928
Women, children...

537
00:57:11,554 --> 00:57:12,847
Well, the thallium
would suggest

538
00:57:12,930 --> 00:57:14,974
that he doesn't like you
very much anymore.

539
00:57:15,057 --> 00:57:16,976
And clearly
the feeling is mutual.

540
00:57:17,017 --> 00:57:19,228
So why don't you tell me
how to find him again?

541
00:57:19,311 --> 00:57:20,312
Oh, come on.

542
00:57:21,397 --> 00:57:22,857
Tell me where he is.

543
00:57:22,940 --> 00:57:24,650
He's everywhere.

544
00:57:24,984 --> 00:57:26,026
Everywhere!

545
00:57:26,402 --> 00:57:28,320
He's sitting
at your desk,

546
00:57:28,362 --> 00:57:31,574
he's kissing your lover,
he's eating supper with your family!

547
00:57:36,495 --> 00:57:37,872
(SIGHS)

548
00:57:38,998 --> 00:57:41,083
You're protecting someone.

549
00:57:42,168 --> 00:57:43,169
Your wife.

550
00:57:43,377 --> 00:57:45,421
(LAUGHING)

551
00:57:46,672 --> 00:57:48,507
She left long ago.

552
00:57:49,216 --> 00:57:50,551
Your son?

553
00:57:54,638 --> 00:57:56,348
Your daughter.

554
00:57:58,726 --> 00:58:00,311
You won't find her.

555
00:58:00,352 --> 00:58:01,854
She's clever.

556
00:58:01,896 --> 00:58:05,024
She's smarter than me.
She knows how to hide.

557
00:58:06,609 --> 00:58:09,111
I can protect her if
you tell me where he is.

558
00:58:09,403 --> 00:58:11,447
(CHUCKLES)

559
00:58:11,780 --> 00:58:13,449
I can keep her alive.

560
00:58:13,532 --> 00:58:14,700
Yeah.

561
00:58:17,620 --> 00:58:18,871
You have my word.

562
00:58:18,954 --> 00:58:20,164
Your word?

563
00:58:21,165 --> 00:58:23,042
The word of an assassin!

564
00:58:35,429 --> 00:58:37,056
That's my word.

565
00:59:04,959 --> 00:59:06,460
<i>L'Américain.</i>

566
00:59:07,503 --> 00:59:09,296
You save her,

567
00:59:09,380 --> 00:59:12,049
she can lead you to <i>L'Américain.</i>
She knows <i>L'Américain.</i>

568
00:59:13,259 --> 00:59:15,344
Try the Hoffler Klinik.

569
00:59:22,142 --> 00:59:26,605
You're a kite dancing in a
hurricane, Mr. Bond.

570
00:59:29,775 --> 00:59:30,943
So long.

571
00:59:31,026 --> 00:59:32,027
(GUNSHOT)

572
01:00:24,246 --> 01:00:27,499
M: I can't deny I'm impressed you
got H.M.G. to cough up for all this.

573
01:00:27,541 --> 01:00:30,002
C: Good God,
the government couldn't
afford this kind of facility.

574
01:00:30,085 --> 01:00:32,796
No, it was benefactors mostly,
from the private sector.

575
01:00:33,339 --> 01:00:34,381
When it goes online,

576
01:00:34,465 --> 01:00:36,258
this building will be
the most sophisticated

577
01:00:36,342 --> 01:00:38,344
data gathering system
in history.

578
01:00:38,385 --> 01:00:41,388
The world's digital ghost,
available 24/7.

579
01:00:41,472 --> 01:00:43,140
George Orwell's
worst nightmare.

580
01:00:43,182 --> 01:00:44,350
I'm glad you like it.

581
01:00:44,850 --> 01:00:47,686
My commiserations
on losing the Nine Eyes vote.

582
01:00:47,770 --> 01:00:48,854
Must have been a blow.

583
01:00:48,937 --> 01:00:51,148
Not really.
Only a matter of time

584
01:00:51,190 --> 01:00:52,441
before the South Africans
see the light.

585
01:00:52,524 --> 01:00:54,735
And you know what they say,
Rome wasn't built in a day.

586
01:00:54,818 --> 01:00:55,819
Day and a half maybe.

587
01:00:56,862 --> 01:01:00,032
Look, Max, I know surveillance
is a fact of life.

588
01:01:01,408 --> 01:01:04,244
It's how you use the
information that concerns me,

589
01:01:04,328 --> 01:01:05,788
and who is using it.

590
01:01:05,871 --> 01:01:07,998
This is what we need to do
to keep the people safe.

591
01:01:08,874 --> 01:01:11,377
Double-0 program
is prehistoric.

592
01:01:12,044 --> 01:01:14,463
Come on, M.
You can't really tell me
that one man in the field

593
01:01:14,546 --> 01:01:16,256
can compete with all of this,

594
01:01:16,340 --> 01:01:19,051
running around out there
with his license to kill.

595
01:01:20,135 --> 01:01:22,304
Have you ever had
to kill a man, Max?

596
01:01:23,931 --> 01:01:25,140
Have you?

597
01:01:25,724 --> 01:01:27,893
To pull that trigger,
you have to be sure.

598
01:01:28,227 --> 01:01:31,980
Yes, you investigate,
analyze, assess, target.

599
01:01:33,065 --> 01:01:35,192
And then you have
to look him in the eye.

600
01:01:36,610 --> 01:01:38,278
And you make the call.

601
01:01:38,737 --> 01:01:41,907
And all the drones, bugs,
cameras, transcripts,

602
01:01:41,990 --> 01:01:43,992
all the surveillance
in the world

603
01:01:44,076 --> 01:01:46,453
can't tell you
what to do next.

604
01:01:48,414 --> 01:01:50,165
A license to kill

605
01:01:50,582 --> 01:01:53,752
is also a license
not to kill.

606
01:01:55,671 --> 01:01:58,090
I didn't want to
have to do this,

607
01:01:59,216 --> 01:02:02,177
but it looks like you still
can't control your agents.

608
01:02:03,429 --> 01:02:05,597
MONEYPENNY: (ON RECORDING)
<i>Bond? I ran that check.</i>

609
01:02:05,639 --> 01:02:07,099
(FAST FORWARDING)

610
01:02:07,141 --> 01:02:09,852
<i>Looks like you've had
dealings with him before.
Quantum.</i>

611
01:02:09,935 --> 01:02:11,729
BOND: <i>Of course. Mr. White!</i>

612
01:02:12,020 --> 01:02:15,274
MONEYPENNY:
<i>Last unconfirmed sighting,
Altaussee in Austria.</i>

613
01:02:15,357 --> 01:02:16,817
BOND: <i>Run another name,
will you?</i>

614
01:02:18,026 --> 01:02:19,236
C: So maybe there's
something to be said

615
01:02:19,278 --> 01:02:21,238
for total surveillance
after all.

616
01:02:24,450 --> 01:02:26,493
You watch MI6 agents?

617
01:02:28,036 --> 01:02:29,705
We watch everyone.

618
01:02:51,810 --> 01:02:53,312
(CAWING)

619
01:03:36,021 --> 01:03:37,356
SWANN:
Please, take a seat.

620
01:03:37,439 --> 01:03:39,483
I'll be with you
in just a moment.

621
01:03:39,733 --> 01:03:41,777
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

622
01:03:55,541 --> 01:03:57,918
Please excuse me,
Mr. Bond.

623
01:04:00,212 --> 01:04:02,714
My name is
Dr. Madeleine Swann.

624
01:04:02,798 --> 01:04:04,633
Our job today is to
analyze your needs,

625
01:04:04,716 --> 01:04:07,219
both psychological
and physical.

626
01:04:07,386 --> 01:04:09,012
Hmm, sounds pretty
straightforward.

627
01:04:10,222 --> 01:04:12,683
I hope you don't mind.
The view can be distracting.

628
01:04:12,724 --> 01:04:14,393
I hadn't noticed.

629
01:04:20,858 --> 01:04:23,485
I see you filled out
most of the paperwork.

630
01:04:23,902 --> 01:04:27,739
Just a few questions to complete
your evaluation, if I may.

631
01:04:28,282 --> 01:04:29,908
Do you exercise?

632
01:04:30,284 --> 01:04:31,493
When I have to.

633
01:04:32,202 --> 01:04:35,247
Do you consider your employment
to be psychologically stressful?

634
01:04:36,248 --> 01:04:37,332
Sometimes.

635
01:04:37,916 --> 01:04:39,376
How much alcohol
do you consume?

636
01:04:40,419 --> 01:04:41,545
Too much.

637
01:04:44,548 --> 01:04:46,008
Some broader questions.

638
01:04:46,091 --> 01:04:48,260
As a child, would you say you
were close to your parents?

639
01:04:48,677 --> 01:04:51,096
My parents died
when I was young.

640
01:04:51,972 --> 01:04:53,599
Really? How old?

641
01:04:54,141 --> 01:04:55,601
Old enough to remember.

642
01:04:55,976 --> 01:04:57,394
How, if I may ask?

643
01:04:57,436 --> 01:04:58,854
It was a climbing accident.

644
01:04:59,688 --> 01:05:00,772
So who brought you up?

645
01:05:00,856 --> 01:05:02,357
Someone else.

646
01:05:03,108 --> 01:05:04,359
Humor me.

647
01:05:05,319 --> 01:05:09,114
How does one train at Oxford and
the Sorbonne become a consultant,

648
01:05:09,156 --> 01:05:12,200
spend two years with
<i>Médecins Sans Frontières</i>

649
01:05:12,284 --> 01:05:13,869
and end up here?

650
01:05:15,037 --> 01:05:17,372
Forgive me,
but anyone might think

651
01:05:17,456 --> 01:05:19,124
you were hiding
from something.

652
01:05:21,084 --> 01:05:23,378
You're paying a lot of money to be
here, Mr. Bond.

653
01:05:23,462 --> 01:05:25,881
Who's asking the questions,
you or me?

654
01:05:25,964 --> 01:05:27,966
Of course. Carry on.

655
01:05:31,553 --> 01:05:34,348
I see you left this
final question blank.

656
01:05:35,098 --> 01:05:36,475
What is your occupation?

657
01:05:36,558 --> 01:05:40,354
Well, that's not the sort of
thing that looks good on a form.

658
01:05:40,562 --> 01:05:41,647
And why is that?

659
01:05:41,730 --> 01:05:42,731
I kill people.

660
01:05:45,901 --> 01:05:47,110
Small world?

661
01:05:49,738 --> 01:05:50,822
Where is he?

662
01:05:51,156 --> 01:05:52,824
Your father's dead.

663
01:05:53,075 --> 01:05:54,576
Two days ago.

664
01:05:54,660 --> 01:05:56,203
(SHUDDERING)
How do you know?

665
01:05:56,286 --> 01:05:57,829
Because I was there.

666
01:05:58,413 --> 01:05:59,498
Did you kill him?

667
01:05:59,581 --> 01:06:00,624
I didn't have to.

668
01:06:01,416 --> 01:06:03,001
He did it himself.

669
01:06:03,835 --> 01:06:06,838
And you came all the way
just to tell me this?

670
01:06:07,464 --> 01:06:08,882
That my father's dead?

671
01:06:09,257 --> 01:06:12,970
I came to tell you that your life
is in danger and I need your help.

672
01:06:13,220 --> 01:06:16,848
- Why?
- I made a deal with him
to protect you.

673
01:06:18,016 --> 01:06:19,476
You're lying.

674
01:06:20,018 --> 01:06:21,353
Why would he trust you?

675
01:06:21,436 --> 01:06:24,481
Because he knew that I
needed something in return.

676
01:06:24,856 --> 01:06:26,108
And what was that?

677
01:06:26,858 --> 01:06:28,276
To find <i>L'Américain.</i>

678
01:06:29,695 --> 01:06:30,988
This interview is over.

679
01:06:31,029 --> 01:06:32,280
Dr. Swann...

680
01:06:32,364 --> 01:06:36,576
You have 10 minutes to leave the building.
Then I'm calling security.

681
01:06:40,205 --> 01:06:41,999
Thank you,
Dr. Swann.

682
01:06:44,793 --> 01:06:46,211
(SIGHS)

683
01:07:04,354 --> 01:07:05,772
Can I get you
something, sir?

684
01:07:05,856 --> 01:07:08,358
Vodka martini.
Shaken, not stirred.

685
01:07:08,400 --> 01:07:10,986
I'm sorry,
we don't serve alcohol.

686
01:07:11,528 --> 01:07:13,697
I'm really starting
to love this place.

687
01:07:13,739 --> 01:07:16,116
He'll have the prolytic
digestive enzyme shake.

688
01:07:16,408 --> 01:07:17,451
Certainly.

689
01:07:17,784 --> 01:07:19,161
If you've come
for the car,

690
01:07:19,244 --> 01:07:20,871
I parked it
at the bottom of the Tiber.

691
01:07:20,912 --> 01:07:23,915
Well, not to worry, 007.
It was only a £3,000,000 prototype.

692
01:07:24,207 --> 01:07:25,375
Why are you here, Q?

693
01:07:25,417 --> 01:07:27,377
Oh, I just fancied a break,
to be honest.

694
01:07:27,419 --> 01:07:29,254
I've been a tad stressed
at work recently.

695
01:07:29,588 --> 01:07:31,548
What with C's people
crawling all over us

696
01:07:31,590 --> 01:07:33,550
and the fact that M wants my
balls for Christmas decorations.

697
01:07:33,592 --> 01:07:35,761
- Get to the point.
- The point, 007,

698
01:07:35,844 --> 01:07:37,929
is that Franz Oberhauser
is dead.

699
01:07:38,013 --> 01:07:39,514
Dead and buried.

700
01:07:39,598 --> 01:07:40,932
And unless you come back
with me right now,

701
01:07:40,974 --> 01:07:43,935
my career and Moneypenny's
will go the same way.

702
01:07:43,977 --> 01:07:46,938
Do you understand?
All hell is breaking
loose out there and...

703
01:07:46,980 --> 01:07:49,608
- I saw him.
- You thought you saw him.

704
01:07:49,691 --> 01:07:51,276
We've been through
the records.

705
01:07:51,359 --> 01:07:53,987
He died in an avalanche
with his father 20 years ago.

706
01:07:54,071 --> 01:07:56,031
Yes. I know that.

707
01:07:56,114 --> 01:07:57,532
But I saw him.

708
01:07:59,618 --> 01:08:01,578
He's not someone
I'll ever forget.

709
01:08:03,080 --> 01:08:05,248
So you have a lead?

710
01:08:05,290 --> 01:08:07,084
I have a name.
<i>L'Américain.</i>

711
01:08:07,167 --> 01:08:10,003
(SCOFFS) Well,
that narrows it down.

712
01:08:10,087 --> 01:08:12,380
Look, I'm sorry, 007,
but time's up.

713
01:08:12,464 --> 01:08:14,508
My whole career
is on the line here.

714
01:08:14,591 --> 01:08:17,010
Either you come back in and do
this through proper channels,

715
01:08:17,094 --> 01:08:18,261
or I go directly to M.

716
01:08:18,303 --> 01:08:20,972
Do one more thing for me.
Then you're out.

717
01:08:22,015 --> 01:08:24,351
Find out what you can
from this.

718
01:08:32,776 --> 01:08:34,319
I really, really
hate you right now.

719
01:08:34,694 --> 01:08:36,196
Thank you, Q.

720
01:08:37,364 --> 01:08:39,491
<i>Monsieur?</i>
Now? Please?

721
01:08:39,533 --> 01:08:40,617
Where are you staying?

722
01:08:40,659 --> 01:08:41,743
The Pevsner. Room 12.

723
01:08:41,827 --> 01:08:43,078
One hour.

724
01:08:44,454 --> 01:08:47,958
Here you are, sir.
One prolytic digestive enzyme shake.

725
01:08:48,208 --> 01:08:49,543
Do me a favor,
will you?

726
01:08:49,626 --> 01:08:51,753
Throw that
down the toilet.

727
01:08:51,837 --> 01:08:53,255
Cut out the middleman.

728
01:09:00,887 --> 01:09:02,681
- (GRUNTS)
- (WHIMPERS)

729
01:09:02,722 --> 01:09:04,057
No! Stay.

730
01:09:54,858 --> 01:09:56,484
What do you want?

731
01:09:59,738 --> 01:10:00,989
What are you doing?

732
01:10:02,616 --> 01:10:04,284
Can't any of you speak?

733
01:10:09,915 --> 01:10:10,916
(EXCLAIMS)

734
01:11:15,605 --> 01:11:17,649
(PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

735
01:12:17,542 --> 01:12:18,626
(EXPLOSION)

736
01:13:10,637 --> 01:13:11,638
(EXCLAIMS)

737
01:13:30,740 --> 01:13:32,283
Come on!

738
01:14:24,836 --> 01:14:26,880
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

739
01:14:31,468 --> 01:14:33,219
Argh, don't touch me!

740
01:14:34,053 --> 01:14:35,054
Hey!

741
01:14:35,346 --> 01:14:38,516
You need to take a breath and calm down.
You're in shock.

742
01:14:38,558 --> 01:14:41,352
Get away from me!
Just get away!

743
01:14:41,478 --> 01:14:43,855
Did it cross your mind
that you led them to me?

744
01:14:49,319 --> 01:14:50,570
I haven't got
time for this.

745
01:14:51,404 --> 01:14:54,532
You need to tell me everything
you know about <i>L'Américain.</i>

746
01:14:54,741 --> 01:14:56,075
Go to hell!

747
01:14:59,204 --> 01:15:00,872
I gave your father my word!

748
01:15:03,208 --> 01:15:06,544
And why should I trust you?
Because my father did?

749
01:15:07,337 --> 01:15:09,547
Because right now,
Dr. Swann,

750
01:15:11,257 --> 01:15:13,885
I'm your best chance
of staying alive.

751
01:15:33,321 --> 01:15:34,489
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

752
01:15:37,158 --> 01:15:38,826
Dr. Swann, Q.

753
01:15:38,910 --> 01:15:40,954
Q, Dr. Swann.

754
01:15:41,663 --> 01:15:43,581
- Hello.
- Enchanted.

755
01:15:45,333 --> 01:15:48,294
Bond, we need
to talk. Alone.

756
01:15:48,378 --> 01:15:49,504
She knows.

757
01:15:49,587 --> 01:15:51,548
- But, Bond...
- She knows.

758
01:15:52,382 --> 01:15:53,508
What have you got?

759
01:15:54,259 --> 01:15:56,427
I owe you an apology, 007.

760
01:15:57,136 --> 01:15:59,138
You are onto something.

761
01:15:59,222 --> 01:16:01,474
Oberhauser is still alive.
The ring proves it.

762
01:16:02,892 --> 01:16:05,270
And it seems they were
all part of one organization.

763
01:16:06,271 --> 01:16:09,941
Le Chiffre, Quantum, Sciarra,
your friend Mr. Silva.

764
01:16:10,275 --> 01:16:11,985
And do you know
who links them all?

765
01:16:12,068 --> 01:16:13,278
BOND: Him.

766
01:16:13,528 --> 01:16:14,862
Exactly.

767
01:16:14,946 --> 01:16:18,366
This organization,
do you know what it's called?

768
01:16:18,825 --> 01:16:19,951
- No.
- SWANN: Spectre.

769
01:16:22,662 --> 01:16:24,872
Its name is Spectre.

770
01:16:25,290 --> 01:16:26,291
How does she know that?

771
01:16:26,374 --> 01:16:28,626
Because my father
was part of it.

772
01:16:29,586 --> 01:16:31,546
Then I think that
you ought to see this.

773
01:16:31,754 --> 01:16:34,340
REPORTER: <i>You're looking at
pictures from South Africa right now</i>

774
01:16:34,424 --> 01:16:36,384
<i>of what appears to be
a huge explosion.</i>

775
01:16:36,467 --> 01:16:39,012
Q, go back to London.

776
01:16:40,346 --> 01:16:43,349
M's gonna need your help.
And keep tracking me.

777
01:16:43,433 --> 01:16:44,642
Q: I will.

778
01:16:45,059 --> 01:16:47,270
And, Bond, you have
to find <i>L'Américain.</i>

779
01:16:48,313 --> 01:16:50,356
He's our only link
to Oberhauser.

780
01:16:50,440 --> 01:16:51,733
It's not a person.

781
01:16:53,067 --> 01:16:54,569
It's a place.

782
01:17:52,710 --> 01:17:54,420
(SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

783
01:17:59,884 --> 01:18:01,219
Thank you.

784
01:18:33,084 --> 01:18:35,086
This is where they spent
their wedding night.

785
01:18:36,921 --> 01:18:38,923
They came back every year.

786
01:18:39,841 --> 01:18:41,718
Then they brought me
with them, too.

787
01:18:45,221 --> 01:18:48,099
He kept coming back,
even after the divorce.

788
01:18:50,476 --> 01:18:52,270
Well, then I'm sorry.

789
01:18:53,271 --> 01:18:54,313
What for?

790
01:18:56,441 --> 01:18:57,650
(CLATTERING)

791
01:19:06,701 --> 01:19:07,702
(GRUNTS)

792
01:19:08,786 --> 01:19:09,787
Ah-ha!

793
01:19:10,455 --> 01:19:11,789
SWANN: What is it?

794
01:19:13,666 --> 01:19:15,543
It's your inheritance.

795
01:19:16,043 --> 01:19:18,379
- Want some?
- No, thank you.

796
01:19:20,131 --> 01:19:22,633
You don't know
what you're missing.

797
01:19:24,552 --> 01:19:25,553
(EXHALES)

798
01:19:31,434 --> 01:19:33,102
This can't be it.

799
01:19:34,312 --> 01:19:36,439
Well, here's to your father.

800
01:19:37,774 --> 01:19:42,320
I promised myself I would never
be hurt by that man again.

801
01:19:43,946 --> 01:19:45,823
I cut off all contact.

802
01:19:46,657 --> 01:19:50,161
I didn't want anything to do
with him or his sick life.

803
01:19:51,329 --> 01:19:53,664
And then,
with his dying breath

804
01:19:54,332 --> 01:19:55,958
he sends me you.

805
01:19:57,293 --> 01:19:58,836
Ironic, no?

806
01:19:58,878 --> 01:20:01,214
You shouldn't be
so hard on him.

807
01:20:01,506 --> 01:20:04,717
The man I just met should
have been dead weeks ago.

808
01:20:04,801 --> 01:20:07,553
The only reason his heart
was still beating was you.

809
01:20:08,805 --> 01:20:11,516
I'll mourn my father
in my own time, Mr. Bond.

810
01:20:12,850 --> 01:20:15,061
And, now,
I'm going to bed.

811
01:20:18,105 --> 01:20:19,273
- (GASPS)
- BOTH: Oh.

812
01:20:22,527 --> 01:20:26,739
Don't think for one moment this
is where I fall into your arms,

813
01:20:27,698 --> 01:20:30,576
seeking solace
for my dead daddy.

814
01:20:34,705 --> 01:20:36,207
You sit there.

815
01:20:36,874 --> 01:20:39,710
Keep watch.
That's what you're good at.

816
01:20:44,507 --> 01:20:47,426
Come anywhere near me
and I'll kill you.

817
01:20:47,677 --> 01:20:49,136
I don't doubt it.

818
01:20:50,304 --> 01:20:51,305
(IMITATES GUNSHOT)

819
01:20:59,981 --> 01:21:02,817
Look. There are two of you.

820
01:21:04,277 --> 01:21:05,820
Two Jameses.

821
01:21:07,238 --> 01:21:08,865
Lucky me.

822
01:21:12,910 --> 01:21:13,953
(WHISPERING IN FRENCH)

823
01:21:14,036 --> 01:21:16,247
What am I doing here?

824
01:21:18,499 --> 01:21:20,501
(SIGHING)

825
01:21:24,171 --> 01:21:26,841
To liars...

826
01:21:26,924 --> 01:21:28,926
...and killers.

827
01:21:28,968 --> 01:21:31,137
To liars...

828
01:21:31,220 --> 01:21:33,264
...and killers...

829
01:21:33,306 --> 01:21:35,308
...everywhere.

830
01:22:00,958 --> 01:22:02,126
(GUN COCKS)

831
01:22:07,256 --> 01:22:09,091
Who sent you?

832
01:22:12,511 --> 01:22:14,221
Who are you working for?

833
01:22:51,884 --> 01:22:53,886
Now, where did you go?

834
01:23:22,665 --> 01:23:24,375
(CHUCKLES) Of course.

835
01:24:47,583 --> 01:24:48,959
What is it?

836
01:24:51,796 --> 01:24:53,089
Nothing.

837
01:25:07,603 --> 01:25:08,854
What's this?

838
01:25:09,522 --> 01:25:11,148
It's coordinates.

839
01:25:14,443 --> 01:25:16,987
Your father was scanning for
a particular satellite phone.

840
01:25:17,071 --> 01:25:19,156
He was looking
for someone.

841
01:25:20,866 --> 01:25:22,785
He was looking for him.

842
01:25:24,411 --> 01:25:26,997
And he sent me here
to finish the job.

843
01:25:28,999 --> 01:25:30,918
- I'm coming with you.
- No, you're not.

844
01:25:32,002 --> 01:25:33,337
I like you alive.

845
01:25:33,379 --> 01:25:34,880
I can look after myself.

846
01:25:34,964 --> 01:25:36,674
That's beside the point.

847
01:25:38,175 --> 01:25:39,802
I might not be coming back.

848
01:25:40,219 --> 01:25:41,428
I know.

849
01:25:42,388 --> 01:25:45,683
But I want to understand
what happened to my father.

850
01:26:03,868 --> 01:26:06,036
So, where was he going?

851
01:26:09,540 --> 01:26:10,958
Nowhere.

852
01:26:23,429 --> 01:26:26,098
Thank you so much. Thanks.
All the very best.

853
01:26:26,182 --> 01:26:27,183
What's going on?

854
01:26:27,224 --> 01:26:29,143
The meeting was brought forward.
Did you not get the message?

855
01:26:29,226 --> 01:26:30,311
No, we didn't.

856
01:26:30,394 --> 01:26:31,562
Shortest meeting
I can remember.

857
01:26:31,854 --> 01:26:33,314
South Africans on board,
I take it?

858
01:26:33,397 --> 01:26:35,232
Yeah, well,
who can blame them?

859
01:26:35,733 --> 01:26:37,902
Nine Eyes is now
officially sanctioned.

860
01:26:37,943 --> 01:26:40,529
The new system goes live
in less than 72 hours.

861
01:26:40,571 --> 01:26:42,573
It's a major step forward.

862
01:26:42,615 --> 01:26:44,450
Global intelligence
cooperation changes everything.

863
01:26:44,533 --> 01:26:46,243
As you said before.

864
01:26:48,078 --> 01:26:49,205
Look.

865
01:26:50,039 --> 01:26:52,208
They've asked me
to head the new committee.

866
01:26:52,249 --> 01:26:54,126
Yes? And?

867
01:26:54,210 --> 01:26:57,838
And I should tell you I've
spoken with the Home Secretary.

868
01:26:58,005 --> 01:27:00,674
And in light of the new
information I've given him,

869
01:27:00,758 --> 01:27:03,802
he's decided to close down
the double-0 program
with immediate effect.

870
01:27:04,261 --> 01:27:05,429
You don't know
what you're doing.

871
01:27:05,512 --> 01:27:07,431
It's not personal.

872
01:27:07,514 --> 01:27:09,099
It's the future.

873
01:27:09,516 --> 01:27:10,768
And...

874
01:27:13,270 --> 01:27:14,271
You're not.

875
01:27:14,313 --> 01:27:16,106
You're a cocky little
bastard, aren't you?

876
01:27:16,315 --> 01:27:17,524
(CHUCKLES)

877
01:27:18,442 --> 01:27:20,069
I'll take that
as a compliment.

878
01:27:20,277 --> 01:27:21,654
I wouldn't.

879
01:27:22,696 --> 01:27:24,406
This isn't over yet.

880
01:27:42,424 --> 01:27:45,678
- Would you press this for me?
Thank you.
- Yes, sir.

881
01:28:04,822 --> 01:28:06,198
Pick it up.

882
01:28:07,449 --> 01:28:08,826
I hate guns.

883
01:28:09,326 --> 01:28:11,662
I promised him
I'd protect you.

884
01:28:11,704 --> 01:28:14,415
The first thing to do is to teach
you how to protect yourself.

885
01:28:14,832 --> 01:28:16,834
What if I shoot you
by mistake?

886
01:28:17,167 --> 01:28:19,295
Wouldn't be the first time.

887
01:28:19,670 --> 01:28:20,921
Pick it up.

888
01:28:21,005 --> 01:28:22,923
I said, I hate guns.

889
01:28:28,595 --> 01:28:30,264
SIG 226.

890
01:28:30,556 --> 01:28:33,183
Front sight.
Rear sight. Hammer.

891
01:28:35,769 --> 01:28:36,937
(SIGHS)

892
01:28:38,981 --> 01:28:41,233
You just point it.
You squeeze the trigger.

893
01:28:41,317 --> 01:28:43,527
You try not to
close your eyes.

894
01:28:44,194 --> 01:28:46,864
Please, try it.

895
01:28:55,205 --> 01:28:56,540
(SIGHS)

896
01:29:12,056 --> 01:29:14,725
I don't have to
teach you anything, do I?

897
01:29:16,727 --> 01:29:19,813
A man once came to our house
to kill my father.

898
01:29:20,481 --> 01:29:23,650
He didn't know I was upstairs
playing in my bedroom.

899
01:29:23,734 --> 01:29:26,070
Or that Papa kept
a Beretta Nine-millimeter

900
01:29:26,111 --> 01:29:28,280
under the sink
with the bleach.

901
01:29:31,575 --> 01:29:33,494
That's why I hate guns.

902
01:29:34,870 --> 01:29:37,456
I think we'll skip
hand-to-hand combat.

903
01:29:55,432 --> 01:29:56,558
MONEYPENNY:
Good evening, sir.

904
01:29:56,600 --> 01:29:58,685
Sorry to interrupt your
supper, but we have some news.

905
01:29:58,769 --> 01:30:00,270
Q: Evening, sir.

906
01:30:00,312 --> 01:30:02,773
Using the Smart Blood,
I've tracked Bond

907
01:30:02,856 --> 01:30:05,401
to a point here
in North Africa.

908
01:30:06,652 --> 01:30:09,321
See, every known map
registers it as empty desert.

909
01:30:09,405 --> 01:30:13,242
Exactly. But if you look at the satellite
blowup, you can clearly see this.

910
01:30:13,575 --> 01:30:14,910
We can't help him.

911
01:30:16,286 --> 01:30:17,746
But, sir, we know
where he's heading.

912
01:30:19,748 --> 01:30:21,625
C is watching
everything we do.

913
01:30:21,708 --> 01:30:24,294
We're only handing them
more information.

914
01:30:27,548 --> 01:30:29,967
Sir, we can't
just desert Bond.

915
01:30:30,008 --> 01:30:32,052
We have to.
We only make him weaker.

916
01:30:32,136 --> 01:30:33,762
But, sir,
we know exactly where he is.

917
01:30:33,804 --> 01:30:36,432
Yes, I know,
but if we can track him,
so can others.

918
01:30:37,266 --> 01:30:39,601
Delete all
the Smart Blood files.

919
01:30:39,643 --> 01:30:40,769
Everything.

920
01:30:42,688 --> 01:30:44,314
He's on his own.

921
01:31:10,674 --> 01:31:12,009
You shouldn't stare.

922
01:31:12,050 --> 01:31:13,969
Well, you shouldn't
look like that.

923
01:31:18,182 --> 01:31:19,933
May I get you
an <i>apéritif?</i>

924
01:31:20,017 --> 01:31:21,351
I'm not sure.

925
01:31:21,393 --> 01:31:24,521
It gets me into trouble.
Makes me do crazy things.

926
01:31:24,563 --> 01:31:26,106
Well, we can't
have that.

927
01:31:26,482 --> 01:31:29,985
So, I'll have
a vodka martini, dirty.

928
01:31:30,319 --> 01:31:31,820
Make that two.

929
01:31:32,821 --> 01:31:34,072
(CHUCKLES)

930
01:31:35,365 --> 01:31:36,825
I have a question.

931
01:31:37,159 --> 01:31:38,368
Well, what's that?

932
01:31:38,452 --> 01:31:41,330
Why, given every
other possible option,

933
01:31:41,705 --> 01:31:44,208
does a man choose the
life of a paid assassin?

934
01:31:44,249 --> 01:31:46,210
Well, it was that
or the priesthood.

935
01:31:46,293 --> 01:31:47,461
(CHUCKLES)

936
01:31:48,378 --> 01:31:51,548
I'm serious.
Is this really what you want?

937
01:31:51,798 --> 01:31:55,469
Living in the shadows?
Hunting? Being hunted?

938
01:31:56,220 --> 01:31:59,181
Always looking behind you?
Always alone?

939
01:31:59,556 --> 01:32:00,807
But I'm not alone.

940
01:32:01,600 --> 01:32:03,268
Answer the question.

941
01:32:04,394 --> 01:32:06,855
I'm not sure I ever
had a choice.

942
01:32:08,232 --> 01:32:10,317
Anyway, I don't stop
to think about it.

943
01:32:10,609 --> 01:32:12,528
What would happen
if you did?

944
01:32:13,362 --> 01:32:15,781
- Stop?
- Yes.

945
01:32:19,785 --> 01:32:21,203
I don't know.

946
01:32:21,870 --> 01:32:23,539
Your drinks, sir.

947
01:32:23,580 --> 01:32:26,083
Could you leave
them there, please.

948
01:32:30,879 --> 01:32:32,506
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

949
01:32:37,302 --> 01:32:39,763
You know,
I think you're wrong.

950
01:32:39,805 --> 01:32:41,139
I am?

951
01:32:42,432 --> 01:32:44,393
We always have a choice.

952
01:32:47,104 --> 01:32:48,814
I'll drink to that.

953
01:33:00,534 --> 01:33:01,577
(GRUNTS)

954
01:33:02,077 --> 01:33:03,078
(GASPS)

955
01:33:03,161 --> 01:33:05,205
(BOTH GRUNTING)

956
01:33:19,761 --> 01:33:20,762
(GRUNTS)

957
01:33:36,320 --> 01:33:37,988
(STRAINING)

958
01:34:37,339 --> 01:34:38,715
(GROANS)

959
01:35:04,908 --> 01:35:05,909
(GUN CLICKS)

960
01:35:11,206 --> 01:35:12,249
(CHOKING)

961
01:35:18,839 --> 01:35:19,923
(GRUNTS)

962
01:35:36,898 --> 01:35:37,899
Shit.

963
01:35:39,276 --> 01:35:41,319
(BOTH PANTING)

964
01:35:46,324 --> 01:35:47,993
What do we do now?

965
01:36:47,427 --> 01:36:49,179
BOND: This might be
a long wait.

966
01:36:51,723 --> 01:36:53,975
Are you having
second thoughts?

967
01:36:54,559 --> 01:36:56,019
Too late now.

968
01:37:15,664 --> 01:37:17,040
What's that?

969
01:37:22,879 --> 01:37:24,381
(COCKING GUN)

970
01:37:32,389 --> 01:37:37,060
That is a 1948
Rolls-Royce Silver Wraith.

971
01:38:01,334 --> 01:38:02,377
Please.

972
01:38:25,442 --> 01:38:27,235
I'm scared, James.

973
01:39:11,071 --> 01:39:13,740
Good afternoon,
Mr. Bond, Dr. Swann.

974
01:39:14,032 --> 01:39:17,827
I want you to know just how excited
we all are to finally meet you.

975
01:39:17,911 --> 01:39:20,664
Well,
it's a pleasure to be here.

976
01:39:20,914 --> 01:39:23,375
Your host invites
you both to rest,

977
01:39:23,458 --> 01:39:25,877
relax, and join him
for drinks at 4:00.

978
01:39:26,252 --> 01:39:28,505
- Tell our host we won't be late.
- MAN: Wonderful.

979
01:39:28,838 --> 01:39:31,591
Before we show you to your
rooms, just one more thing.

980
01:39:39,349 --> 01:39:40,517
Oh.

981
01:39:43,269 --> 01:39:44,938
You be careful
with that.

982
01:39:45,814 --> 01:39:47,315
It's loaded.

983
01:39:53,863 --> 01:39:55,198
Thank you.

984
01:40:54,382 --> 01:40:56,593
MAN: This is
a very special place.

985
01:40:57,093 --> 01:41:00,430
He has requested
you enter it alone.

986
01:41:00,930 --> 01:41:02,265
Of course.

987
01:41:04,768 --> 01:41:06,102
Champagne?

988
01:41:07,437 --> 01:41:08,855
Maybe later.

989
01:41:09,564 --> 01:41:10,899
Certainly.

990
01:41:23,286 --> 01:41:24,662
(DOOR WHIRRING SOFTLY)

991
01:41:42,305 --> 01:41:44,849
BOND: (SOFTLY) I think
we're meant to be impressed.

992
01:41:57,779 --> 01:41:59,030
OBERHAUSER: Touch it.

993
01:42:00,698 --> 01:42:02,909
You can touch it
if you want.

994
01:42:05,120 --> 01:42:06,955
Do you know what it is?

995
01:42:06,996 --> 01:42:08,665
It's a meteorite.

996
01:42:09,791 --> 01:42:11,501
OBERHAUSER: Yes, exactly.

997
01:42:12,001 --> 01:42:15,797
The Kartenhoff.
The oldest in human possession.

998
01:42:16,965 --> 01:42:19,801
The very meteorite
which made this crater.

999
01:42:21,636 --> 01:42:22,846
Think about it.

1000
01:42:23,513 --> 01:42:27,142
So many years up there,
alone, silent,

1001
01:42:28,309 --> 01:42:32,230
building momentum until it
chose to make its mark on Earth.

1002
01:42:34,023 --> 01:42:36,734
A huge, unstoppable force.

1003
01:42:37,318 --> 01:42:39,654
Except it did stop,
didn't it?

1004
01:42:40,155 --> 01:42:41,531
Right here.

1005
01:42:56,004 --> 01:42:59,883
I can't tell you how much I've
been looking forward to this.

1006
01:42:59,924 --> 01:43:02,218
All of us here, together.

1007
01:43:05,013 --> 01:43:06,556
A reunion.

1008
01:43:08,725 --> 01:43:11,561
I'm so glad you came,
too, dear Madeleine.

1009
01:43:13,354 --> 01:43:16,191
You were just a girl
when I saw you first.

1010
01:43:17,567 --> 01:43:20,528
I came to your home once
to see your father.

1011
01:43:23,072 --> 01:43:24,741
I don't remember that.

1012
01:43:26,034 --> 01:43:27,410
But I do.

1013
01:43:28,203 --> 01:43:29,746
(DOOR WHIRRING SOFTLY)

1014
01:43:32,081 --> 01:43:33,291
Shall we?

1015
01:43:37,253 --> 01:43:38,504
SWANN:
What is this place?

1016
01:43:39,255 --> 01:43:40,673
Information.

1017
01:43:43,927 --> 01:43:45,678
Information is all,

1018
01:43:46,971 --> 01:43:48,306
is it not?

1019
01:43:49,557 --> 01:43:50,975
For example,

1020
01:43:51,059 --> 01:43:55,647
you must know by now that the
double-0 program is officially dead.

1021
01:43:55,855 --> 01:44:00,109
(CHUCKLES) Which leads me to
speculate exactly why you came.

1022
01:44:03,404 --> 01:44:06,282
So, James,
why did you come?

1023
01:44:06,783 --> 01:44:08,451
I came here to kill you.

1024
01:44:09,452 --> 01:44:11,788
And I thought you
came here to die.

1025
01:44:12,121 --> 01:44:14,165
Well, it's all
a matter of perspective.

1026
01:44:15,792 --> 01:44:17,669
Speaking of perspective.

1027
01:44:35,478 --> 01:44:38,815
- Is this live?
- MAN: Live and direct.
16:20 GMT.

1028
01:44:40,108 --> 01:44:42,360
OBERHAUSER: What an
uncanny coincidence.

1029
01:44:42,443 --> 01:44:46,906
<i>The French have a saying,
"It's the fate of glass to break."</i>

1030
01:44:46,990 --> 01:44:51,077
<i>Well, maybe it's the fate
of spies to just disappear.</i>

1031
01:44:51,286 --> 01:44:52,996
<i>But with any luck,</i>

1032
01:44:53,329 --> 01:44:55,373
<i>we leave something behind.</i>

1033
01:44:55,623 --> 01:44:59,127
<i>In the meantime,
I'm sure C will keep you all busy.</i>

1034
01:44:59,877 --> 01:45:01,504
<i>Thank you all.</i>

1035
01:45:02,130 --> 01:45:03,923
(SCATTERED APPLAUSE)

1036
01:45:05,300 --> 01:45:08,136
That's touching,
don't you think?

1037
01:45:11,306 --> 01:45:12,974
Well, James,

1038
01:45:13,683 --> 01:45:15,977
it looks like
you're all alone.

1039
01:45:16,019 --> 01:45:18,646
Not much more than a
voyeur, are you?

1040
01:45:19,689 --> 01:45:21,691
Too scared to join in.

1041
01:45:22,025 --> 01:45:23,609
(CHUCKLING) I don't think
you quite understand.

1042
01:45:23,693 --> 01:45:25,153
Oh, I think I do.

1043
01:45:25,194 --> 01:45:27,989
You set cities on fire and
watch innocent people burn,

1044
01:45:28,031 --> 01:45:30,241
so you can convince
governments to join

1045
01:45:30,325 --> 01:45:32,994
an intelligence network
you've paid for.

1046
01:45:33,036 --> 01:45:34,871
Not that complicated.

1047
01:45:35,580 --> 01:45:39,375
I'm guessing our little friend, C,
he's one of your disciples.

1048
01:45:40,835 --> 01:45:42,545
You could say that.

1049
01:45:42,754 --> 01:45:44,339
And what does
he get out of it?

1050
01:45:45,340 --> 01:45:46,549
Nothing.

1051
01:45:47,175 --> 01:45:49,010
He's a visionary,
like me.

1052
01:45:49,052 --> 01:45:50,720
Visionaries.

1053
01:45:51,512 --> 01:45:53,389
Psychiatric wards
are full of them.

1054
01:45:53,514 --> 01:45:56,434
Whereas you couldn't see
what's right in front of you.

1055
01:45:56,517 --> 01:46:00,521
You came across me so many
times and yet you never saw me.

1056
01:46:01,064 --> 01:46:03,524
Le Chiffre, Greene, Silva.

1057
01:46:03,566 --> 01:46:04,734
All dead.

1058
01:46:04,776 --> 01:46:05,902
Yeah, that's right.

1059
01:46:06,194 --> 01:46:07,695
A nice pattern developed.

1060
01:46:07,737 --> 01:46:11,199
You interfered in my world,
I destroyed yours.

1061
01:46:13,076 --> 01:46:14,660
Or did you think
it was coincidence

1062
01:46:14,744 --> 01:46:17,288
that all the women in
your life ended up dead?

1063
01:46:18,748 --> 01:46:20,833
Vesper Lynd,
for example.

1064
01:46:22,293 --> 01:46:25,713
She was the big one.
Has he told you about her?

1065
01:46:28,049 --> 01:46:31,219
And then, of course,
your beloved M.

1066
01:46:32,095 --> 01:46:34,097
Gone forever.

1067
01:46:38,226 --> 01:46:39,394
Me.

1068
01:46:41,270 --> 01:46:43,398
It was all me, James.

1069
01:46:43,439 --> 01:46:47,235
It's always been me.
The author of all your pain.

1070
01:46:51,072 --> 01:46:53,449
You're a brave
woman, my dear.

1071
01:47:00,790 --> 01:47:03,960
Now I understand why
my father lost his mind.

1072
01:47:04,293 --> 01:47:07,171
He didn't lose his mind,
he was just weak.

1073
01:47:07,255 --> 01:47:09,257
But at least he understood
what he was up against.

1074
01:47:09,632 --> 01:47:12,844
You see, they failed to
comprehend the crucial fact,

1075
01:47:12,927 --> 01:47:16,639
that a terrible event can
lead to something wonderful.

1076
01:47:18,975 --> 01:47:20,977
Since you mention your father,
I'll show you.

1077
01:47:21,978 --> 01:47:24,522
WHITE: (OVER RECORDING) <i>She's clever.
She's smarter than me.</i>

1078
01:47:24,605 --> 01:47:25,815
<i>She knows how to hide.</i>

1079
01:47:28,151 --> 01:47:31,070
BOND: <i>I can protect her if
you tell me where he is.</i>

1080
01:47:31,154 --> 01:47:33,156
(WHITE LAUGHING)

1081
01:47:33,448 --> 01:47:35,158
BOND: <i>I can keep her alive.</i>

1082
01:47:35,199 --> 01:47:36,409
WHITE: <i>Yeah.</i>

1083
01:47:36,492 --> 01:47:37,702
BOND: <i>You have my word.</i>

1084
01:47:37,785 --> 01:47:39,745
No, no, no. Turn this off.

1085
01:47:39,829 --> 01:47:41,414
WHITE: <i>Your word?</i>

1086
01:47:41,998 --> 01:47:43,416
<i>The word of an assassin!</i>

1087
01:47:43,499 --> 01:47:44,834
Turn this off.

1088
01:47:45,001 --> 01:47:47,003
- This is important.
- I said turn it off!

1089
01:47:47,670 --> 01:47:48,671
(GRUNTING)

1090
01:47:49,630 --> 01:47:52,133
I want you to
understand something.

1091
01:48:02,018 --> 01:48:03,686
BOND: <i>That's my word.</i>

1092
01:48:04,979 --> 01:48:06,105
Madeleine?

1093
01:48:06,606 --> 01:48:08,024
Look at me.

1094
01:48:09,192 --> 01:48:12,612
Don't look at him,
Madeleine. Look at me.

1095
01:48:14,489 --> 01:48:15,990
WHITE: <i>L'Américain.</i>

1096
01:48:17,200 --> 01:48:18,743
<i>You save her,</i>

1097
01:48:19,118 --> 01:48:22,205
<i>she can lead you to L'Américain.
She knows L'Américain.</i>

1098
01:48:24,999 --> 01:48:27,043
<i>Try the Hoffler Klinik.</i>

1099
01:48:33,549 --> 01:48:37,887
<i>You're a kite dancing in a
hurricane, Mr. Bond.</i>

1100
01:48:41,057 --> 01:48:42,391
<i>So long.</i>

1101
01:48:43,434 --> 01:48:44,560
(GUNSHOT)

1102
01:48:49,565 --> 01:48:52,902
The things that
bring people together.

1103
01:48:56,864 --> 01:48:59,492
Out of horror, beauty.

1104
01:49:12,505 --> 01:49:14,507
(PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

1105
01:49:26,060 --> 01:49:28,896
OBERHAUSER: Torture is easy,
on a superficial level.

1106
01:49:28,938 --> 01:49:32,066
A man can watch himself
being disemboweled

1107
01:49:32,567 --> 01:49:35,778
and derive great horror
from the experience,

1108
01:49:35,820 --> 01:49:38,447
but it's still
going on at a distance.

1109
01:49:38,614 --> 01:49:41,367
It isn't taking
place where he is.

1110
01:49:42,118 --> 01:49:47,790
As you know all too well,
dear Madeleine,
a man lives inside his head.

1111
01:49:48,249 --> 01:49:51,043
That's where
the seat of his soul is.

1112
01:49:52,378 --> 01:49:54,839
Now, James and I were
both present recently

1113
01:49:54,922 --> 01:49:57,425
when a man was
deprived of his eyes.

1114
01:49:58,426 --> 01:50:01,721
And the most
astonishing thing happened.

1115
01:50:01,804 --> 01:50:02,930
Didn't you notice?

1116
01:50:03,472 --> 01:50:05,641
He wasn't there anymore.

1117
01:50:05,975 --> 01:50:08,352
He'd gone even though
he was still alive.

1118
01:50:08,436 --> 01:50:12,315
So in this brief moment
between life and death,

1119
01:50:12,398 --> 01:50:15,234
there was nobody
inside his skull.

1120
01:50:16,777 --> 01:50:18,112
Most odd.

1121
01:50:20,031 --> 01:50:21,407
So, James.

1122
01:50:21,490 --> 01:50:22,825
(CHAIR WHIRRING)

1123
01:50:23,326 --> 01:50:26,162
I'm going to penetrate

1124
01:50:26,954 --> 01:50:29,332
to where you are.

1125
01:50:30,124 --> 01:50:32,335
To the inside
of your head.

1126
01:50:33,419 --> 01:50:36,172
Now, the first probe
will play with your sight,

1127
01:50:36,547 --> 01:50:37,673
your hearing

1128
01:50:38,299 --> 01:50:40,468
and your balance,

1129
01:50:40,509 --> 01:50:43,346
just with the subtlest
of manipulations.

1130
01:50:43,512 --> 01:50:45,556
Well, get on with it then.

1131
01:50:46,182 --> 01:50:49,518
Nothing can be as painful
as listening to you talk.

1132
01:50:50,311 --> 01:50:51,646
All right.

1133
01:50:52,438 --> 01:50:53,856
Let's begin.

1134
01:50:53,939 --> 01:50:55,566
(WHIRRING)

1135
01:51:07,787 --> 01:51:09,580
(SCREAMING)

1136
01:51:11,916 --> 01:51:13,668
(WHIMPERING)

1137
01:51:21,509 --> 01:51:23,803
(GROANING LOUDLY)

1138
01:51:26,514 --> 01:51:28,516
Why are you doing this?

1139
01:51:41,696 --> 01:51:43,864
You probably know
that James here

1140
01:51:43,906 --> 01:51:46,033
lost his parents
when he was young.

1141
01:51:49,370 --> 01:51:51,831
But did you know
that it was my father

1142
01:51:51,914 --> 01:51:54,291
who helped him through
this difficult time?

1143
01:52:02,466 --> 01:52:04,468
Over the course
of two winters

1144
01:52:04,552 --> 01:52:08,764
he taught him to ski,
and climb, and hunt.

1145
01:52:09,557 --> 01:52:13,936
He soothed the wounds of the
poor little blue-eyed orphan.

1146
01:52:14,895 --> 01:52:16,564
(PANTING)

1147
01:52:16,605 --> 01:52:19,275
Asked me to treat
him as a brother.

1148
01:52:19,775 --> 01:52:21,527
My little brother.

1149
01:52:23,112 --> 01:52:25,114
They formed
quite an attachment.

1150
01:52:26,782 --> 01:52:27,908
So,

1151
01:52:28,743 --> 01:52:29,952
you killed him.

1152
01:52:31,454 --> 01:52:32,955
Yes, I did.

1153
01:52:36,459 --> 01:52:39,128
You know what
happens when a cuckoo

1154
01:52:39,211 --> 01:52:42,131
hatches inside
another bird's nest?

1155
01:52:43,424 --> 01:52:44,592
Yes.

1156
01:52:45,634 --> 01:52:48,095
It forces
the other eggs out.

1157
01:52:48,137 --> 01:52:49,180
OBERHAUSER: Yes.

1158
01:52:49,472 --> 01:52:54,477
Well, this cuckoo made me realize
my father's life had to end.

1159
01:52:55,811 --> 01:52:58,397
In a way, he's responsible
for the path I took.

1160
01:52:58,647 --> 01:53:01,317
So, thank you.
(SING-SONG) Cuckoo.

1161
01:53:03,360 --> 01:53:04,779
(CHUCKLING)

1162
01:53:07,156 --> 01:53:10,075
Do you know any other
birdcalls, Franz?

1163
01:53:10,201 --> 01:53:12,244
(BOND CHUCKLING)

1164
01:53:17,625 --> 01:53:18,959
Hello, pussy.

1165
01:53:21,670 --> 01:53:25,299
Franz Oberhauser died
20 years ago, James.

1166
01:53:25,341 --> 01:53:28,093
In an avalanche,
alongside his father.

1167
01:53:29,345 --> 01:53:33,766
The man you are talking to
now, the man inside your head,

1168
01:53:34,517 --> 01:53:37,102
is Ernst Stavro Blofeld.

1169
01:53:37,520 --> 01:53:38,979
Catchy name.

1170
01:53:39,522 --> 01:53:41,524
My mother's bloodline.

1171
01:53:42,983 --> 01:53:47,196
If the needle finds the correct
spot in the fusiform gyrus,

1172
01:53:47,696 --> 01:53:49,698
you'll recognize no one.

1173
01:53:49,949 --> 01:53:51,575
(CHUCKLING) Of course,
the faces of your women

1174
01:53:51,659 --> 01:53:53,536
are interchangeable,
aren't they, James?

1175
01:53:55,704 --> 01:53:57,331
You won't know
who she is.

1176
01:53:57,373 --> 01:54:00,626
Just another passing face
on your way to the grave.

1177
01:54:09,343 --> 01:54:12,054
He dies not knowing
who you are.

1178
01:54:14,348 --> 01:54:16,225
The daughter
of an assassin.

1179
01:54:16,851 --> 01:54:18,853
The only one who could
have understood him.

1180
01:54:20,020 --> 01:54:21,397
- Shame.
- (KEYBOARD CLACKING)

1181
01:54:24,024 --> 01:54:25,359
(WHIRRING)

1182
01:54:26,610 --> 01:54:28,153
(GRUNTING)

1183
01:54:32,783 --> 01:54:34,827
- (GROANING)
- (WHIRRING INTENSIFIES)

1184
01:54:36,287 --> 01:54:38,330
(WHIMPERING)

1185
01:54:45,087 --> 01:54:47,089
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1186
01:54:58,309 --> 01:54:59,768
I love you.

1187
01:55:05,065 --> 01:55:07,526
BLOFELD: Do those blue eyes
still recognize you?

1188
01:55:11,947 --> 01:55:14,742
I'd recognize
you anywhere.

1189
01:55:16,994 --> 01:55:18,329
The watch.

1190
01:55:33,802 --> 01:55:35,179
One minute.

1191
01:55:36,639 --> 01:55:38,098
One minute.

1192
01:55:42,144 --> 01:55:43,938
BLOFELD: Did he say something?

1193
01:55:43,979 --> 01:55:45,314
<i>Tempus fugit.</i>

1194
01:55:47,149 --> 01:55:49,818
- What?
- (SOFTLY) <i>Tempus fugit.</i>

1195
01:55:50,319 --> 01:55:52,321
I can't hear you, James.

1196
01:55:54,698 --> 01:55:56,033
BOND: I said,

1197
01:55:56,825 --> 01:55:58,661
doesn't time fly?

1198
01:55:58,744 --> 01:56:00,162
(DRILLS WHIRRING)

1199
01:56:22,184 --> 01:56:23,435
(GUNFIRE)

1200
01:56:25,980 --> 01:56:27,314
In there!

1201
01:57:08,897 --> 01:57:10,399
Let's go home.

1202
01:57:11,108 --> 01:57:13,027
(EXPLODING)

1203
01:57:26,582 --> 01:57:28,250
It's not over yet.

1204
01:58:18,092 --> 01:58:19,676
Q: I've never even
heard of Hildebrand.

1205
01:58:19,760 --> 01:58:22,971
M: That is the general
idea with safe houses.

1206
01:58:39,947 --> 01:58:41,573
Exactly how safe
is this, sir?

1207
01:58:41,657 --> 01:58:43,492
We're about to find out.

1208
01:58:46,954 --> 01:58:48,455
It's safe.

1209
01:58:48,497 --> 01:58:50,165
Better wait here.

1210
01:58:53,627 --> 01:58:54,795
I'm M.

1211
01:58:54,837 --> 01:58:55,879
Madeleine Swann.

1212
01:58:55,963 --> 01:58:56,964
Pleased to meet you.

1213
01:58:57,005 --> 01:58:58,841
So, what do you
have for me, 007?

1214
01:58:58,924 --> 01:59:02,970
The recently deceased head of
Spectre, Ernst Stavro Blofeld,

1215
01:59:03,637 --> 01:59:07,474
and his chief of intelligence,
your new best friend, C.

1216
01:59:08,851 --> 01:59:11,854
About to take control of his very
own global surveillance system

1217
01:59:11,937 --> 01:59:14,481
that he built right
here under our noses.

1218
01:59:14,523 --> 01:59:16,942
Then we'd better move.
The system goes online at midnight.

1219
01:59:17,359 --> 01:59:20,237
BOND: If that happens,
Spectre will have control of everything.

1220
01:59:20,320 --> 01:59:22,281
So, you and I will
have a quiet word with C

1221
01:59:22,364 --> 01:59:25,033
while Q hacks into the system
and stops it going online.

1222
01:59:25,659 --> 01:59:26,702
It won't be easy.

1223
01:59:26,743 --> 01:59:29,163
He'll find a way.
He always does.

1224
01:59:33,959 --> 01:59:35,836
It's good to
have you back, 007.

1225
01:59:36,712 --> 01:59:37,796
Sir.

1226
01:59:47,389 --> 01:59:49,224
James, I can't.

1227
01:59:49,975 --> 01:59:52,895
I'll come back for you
when it's all over.

1228
01:59:53,896 --> 01:59:55,480
No, I can't.

1229
01:59:55,898 --> 01:59:57,900
No, you can't
stay here, or you...

1230
01:59:58,567 --> 02:00:02,779
I can't go back to this life.
And I'm not going to ask you to change.

1231
02:00:03,488 --> 02:00:04,990
This is who you are.

1232
02:00:07,743 --> 02:00:09,286
You're saying good-bye.

1233
02:00:10,078 --> 02:00:11,205
Yes.

1234
02:00:13,373 --> 02:00:14,708
Take care.

1235
02:00:17,127 --> 02:00:19,129
You're a good man, James.

1236
02:01:20,315 --> 02:01:21,858
Are you in yet, Q?

1237
02:01:22,317 --> 02:01:24,653
A few layers of impenetrable
security still to go,

1238
02:01:24,695 --> 02:01:26,655
<i>but I think
I'm getting somewhere.</i>

1239
02:02:15,120 --> 02:02:16,663
They've seen us! Reverse!

1240
02:02:16,913 --> 02:02:18,498
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1241
02:02:56,578 --> 02:02:57,746
Go!

1242
02:03:08,799 --> 02:03:10,759
Get him in the building!

1243
02:03:10,884 --> 02:03:13,053
Move. Move!

1244
02:03:14,012 --> 02:03:15,305
(GUNSHOTS)

1245
02:04:32,007 --> 02:04:35,552
Go back and find M, now!
We need them both.

1246
02:04:45,020 --> 02:04:47,856
Not a good feeling
being watched, is it?

1247
02:04:52,527 --> 02:04:54,446
Don't tell me you're
responsible for this.

1248
02:04:54,529 --> 02:04:57,407
No, but my Quartermaster is.

1249
02:04:57,491 --> 02:04:59,242
And he's
extremely talented.

1250
02:04:59,326 --> 02:05:00,368
C: Well, bravo.

1251
02:05:00,452 --> 02:05:04,873
But in case you hadn't realized it,
you two are out of a job.

1252
02:05:04,956 --> 02:05:06,208
So you're trespassing.

1253
02:05:06,249 --> 02:05:08,710
I'm afraid you've got the
wrong end of the stick, Max.

1254
02:05:08,793 --> 02:05:11,546
We're going to stop this
system going online.

1255
02:05:11,630 --> 02:05:13,006
And then I'm going
to bring you in.

1256
02:05:13,131 --> 02:05:14,674
On what grounds exactly?

1257
02:05:14,966 --> 02:05:16,885
Poor taste in friends.

1258
02:05:53,213 --> 02:05:55,632
Take a look at the world.

1259
02:05:57,217 --> 02:05:58,385
Chaos.

1260
02:05:59,511 --> 02:06:01,429
Because people like you,

1261
02:06:01,513 --> 02:06:02,931
paper-pushers
and politicians,

1262
02:06:03,056 --> 02:06:06,601
are too spineless to do
what needs to be done.

1263
02:06:07,060 --> 02:06:10,564
So I made an alliance to put
the power where it should be.

1264
02:06:10,605 --> 02:06:15,610
And now you want to throw it
away for the sake of "democracy."

1265
02:06:16,236 --> 02:06:17,904
Whatever the hell that is.

1266
02:06:18,446 --> 02:06:21,074
How predictably moronic.

1267
02:06:21,116 --> 02:06:24,452
But then isn't that
what M stands for?

1268
02:06:26,288 --> 02:06:28,248
- "Moron."
- (GUN CLICKS)

1269
02:06:29,332 --> 02:06:31,668
And now we know
what C stands for.

1270
02:06:36,298 --> 02:06:37,632
"Careless."

1271
02:06:46,182 --> 02:06:47,809
(CLANGING)

1272
02:06:50,645 --> 02:06:51,855
(CLANGING)

1273
02:07:16,921 --> 02:07:18,548
Come on.

1274
02:07:18,673 --> 02:07:20,425
- (BEEPS)
- No, no, no!

1275
02:08:24,698 --> 02:08:27,992
You're a hard man
to kill, Blofeld.

1276
02:08:34,416 --> 02:08:36,584
Ouch.

1277
02:08:37,168 --> 02:08:38,920
I do hope that
doesn't hurt too much.

1278
02:08:40,213 --> 02:08:43,717
My wounds will heal.

1279
02:08:43,758 --> 02:08:45,385
What about yours?

1280
02:08:46,928 --> 02:08:49,264
Look around you,
James. Look.

1281
02:08:49,723 --> 02:08:51,891
This is what's
left of your world.

1282
02:08:52,183 --> 02:08:56,396
Everything you ever
stood for, everything
you believed in, a ruin.

1283
02:08:57,564 --> 02:09:00,066
Why are we here?

1284
02:09:01,317 --> 02:09:03,069
Did you miss me?

1285
02:09:03,945 --> 02:09:05,238
No.

1286
02:09:11,870 --> 02:09:14,956
But I know someone who does.

1287
02:09:22,130 --> 02:09:24,215
Where is she?

1288
02:09:25,008 --> 02:09:27,469
That's for you to find out.

1289
02:09:34,976 --> 02:09:37,979
In three minutes,
this building will be demolished.

1290
02:09:39,063 --> 02:09:41,316
I can get out easily.

1291
02:09:41,399 --> 02:09:43,485
Now, you have a choice.

1292
02:09:43,526 --> 02:09:46,112
Die trying to save her or

1293
02:09:46,154 --> 02:09:48,531
save yourself and
live with the pain.

1294
02:09:49,699 --> 02:09:50,825
You're bluffing.

1295
02:09:53,411 --> 02:09:54,496
Am I?

1296
02:09:58,583 --> 02:09:59,709
(LAUGHING)

1297
02:10:02,170 --> 02:10:04,047
(CHUCKLING)
I've really put you
through it, haven't I?

1298
02:10:05,799 --> 02:10:07,342
That's brothers for you.

1299
02:10:08,343 --> 02:10:11,805
They always know
which buttons to press.

1300
02:10:11,971 --> 02:10:14,224
(ALARM BLARING)

1301
02:10:24,192 --> 02:10:26,236
Madeleine!

1302
02:10:31,491 --> 02:10:33,243
- Come on.
- (KEYBOARD CLACKING)

1303
02:10:33,618 --> 02:10:34,619
Come on.

1304
02:10:36,162 --> 02:10:37,622
Yes!

1305
02:10:39,249 --> 02:10:40,625
Let's go.

1306
02:10:41,334 --> 02:10:42,335
After you.

1307
02:10:52,762 --> 02:10:56,015
Why can't you
just face it, M?

1308
02:10:57,100 --> 02:10:58,560
You don't matter anymore.

1309
02:10:59,394 --> 02:11:01,479
Maybe I don't.

1310
02:11:01,563 --> 02:11:02,730
But something has to.

1311
02:11:48,151 --> 02:11:49,652
(BEEPING)

1312
02:11:57,702 --> 02:11:58,703
Dead.

1313
02:11:58,912 --> 02:12:00,288
- Any word on Bond?
- MONEYPENNY: No.

1314
02:12:00,455 --> 02:12:02,290
But I can hazard a guess.

1315
02:12:10,048 --> 02:12:12,133
Madeleine!

1316
02:12:14,344 --> 02:12:16,387
Madeleine!

1317
02:12:32,946 --> 02:12:34,697
(THUDDING)

1318
02:12:35,073 --> 02:12:36,366
(SWANN SCREAMING)

1319
02:12:54,425 --> 02:12:55,677
(BEEPING CONTINUES)

1320
02:13:01,182 --> 02:13:02,308
Do you trust me?

1321
02:13:02,684 --> 02:13:03,768
Do I have a choice?

1322
02:13:03,851 --> 02:13:04,852
Not anymore.

1323
02:13:10,108 --> 02:13:11,693
(GRUNTING)

1324
02:13:15,697 --> 02:13:17,031
Come on!

1325
02:13:32,046 --> 02:13:33,965
Good-bye, James Bond.

1326
02:13:49,355 --> 02:13:51,733
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1327
02:14:36,778 --> 02:14:37,987
(BULLET RICOCHETING)

1328
02:14:52,168 --> 02:14:53,294
(BULLET RICOCHETING)

1329
02:15:03,763 --> 02:15:05,389
(ALARM BEEPING)

1330
02:15:26,369 --> 02:15:27,537
(ALARM BLARING)

1331
02:15:36,671 --> 02:15:38,214
Brace, brace, brace!

1332
02:15:38,756 --> 02:15:40,049
(BREATHING HARD)

1333
02:15:43,678 --> 02:15:44,804
(GRUNTS)

1334
02:15:54,438 --> 02:15:56,315
(ALARM CONTINUES BLARING)

1335
02:16:03,865 --> 02:16:05,032
(GRUNTING)

1336
02:16:07,869 --> 02:16:09,036
(YELLS)

1337
02:16:17,378 --> 02:16:19,213
(SIREN WAILING)

1338
02:16:28,264 --> 02:16:29,849
(STRAINING)

1339
02:16:46,073 --> 02:16:47,366
Sir, this is
a terrorist alert.

1340
02:16:47,408 --> 02:16:48,576
Mallory, double-0 section.

1341
02:16:51,871 --> 02:16:53,831
Stand them down.

1342
02:16:55,249 --> 02:16:56,751
Echo team, hold fire.

1343
02:16:57,084 --> 02:16:59,337
Stand down.

1344
02:17:06,969 --> 02:17:08,721
(GRUNTING)

1345
02:17:34,830 --> 02:17:35,957
Finish it.

1346
02:17:47,510 --> 02:17:49,220
Finish it.

1347
02:17:53,224 --> 02:17:54,308
(RELEASING CLIP)

1348
02:17:55,893 --> 02:17:56,978
(COCKS GUN)

1349
02:18:01,774 --> 02:18:03,234
Out of bullets.

1350
02:18:20,126 --> 02:18:22,169
And besides,

1351
02:18:22,503 --> 02:18:24,505
I've got something
better to do.

1352
02:19:10,968 --> 02:19:13,179
Under the Special
Measures Act of 2001,

1353
02:19:13,220 --> 02:19:16,140
I am detaining you on behalf
of Her Majesty's Government.

1354
02:19:57,932 --> 02:19:59,892
(KEYBOARD CLACKING)

1355
02:20:03,479 --> 02:20:05,314
(ELEVATOR DESCENDING)

1356
02:20:22,248 --> 02:20:23,541
Bond?

1357
02:20:27,461 --> 02:20:28,546
(STAMMERING)

1358
02:20:28,629 --> 02:20:30,631
- What are you doing here?
- Good morning, Q.

1359
02:20:38,514 --> 02:20:39,723
I thought you'd gone.

1360
02:20:39,807 --> 02:20:40,933
I have.

1361
02:20:42,810 --> 02:20:45,062
There's just
one thing I need.

1362
02:20:49,525 --> 02:20:52,069
(ENGINE REVVING)